  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed combinations. Thirteen credibility factors were assessed; the assessment team concluded that the accumulated evidence, including mesh-independence studies, solver benchmarks, and physiologically representative boundary conditions, collectively supports a Medium assurance level. The decision record reflects acceptance by the credibility assessment team on the basis of the totality of evidence reviewed.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
