    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 factors. While several factors achieved levels below their MRL-5 requirements, the team concluded that the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, the physiologically representative test conditions, and the direct traceability of NIH to the regulatory threshold collectively provide sufficient confidence to support a Medium assurance level and an Accepted decision. Residual gaps in discretization error and model form uncertainty are noted as areas for future study but were judged not to invalidate the overall credibility conclusion.",
